TYPHOON LAGOON was taken in hand while in tight between foes briefly in the early going, traveled three wide on the first turn, was reserved on the outside towards the rear, bobbled outside the five-eighths, went three wide on the far turn, came four wide into the stretch then quickly shifted to the six path and failed to threaten. JUAN VALDEZ saved ground on the first turn, was unhurried while reserved towards the rear, raced between foes in the two path on the far turn, was asked for his best in upper stretch and lacked the needed response. AMERICAN HUSTLE moved in early while taken under a tight hold, threw his head while becoming rank on the initial straightaway, was hard held in the two to three path going around the opening bend, stalked the pace on the outside, was let out in the two path on the far turn, made a bid with three furlongs to run, turned into the stretch between foes, chased into the final furlong and came up empty. ROCKSTAR RED moved in while going to the front, went around the first turn in the two path, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked while inside on the far turn, lost the lead near the quarter-pole and gave way.
